'Cyclohexanehexone', also known as 'hexaketocyclohexane' and 'triquinoyl', is
an organic compound with formula C 6O 6, the sixfold ketone
of cyclohexane. It is an oxide of carbon (an oxocarbon), indeed a hexamer of
carbon monoxide.

As of May 2006, this compound had yet to be synthesized in bulk.
